.name
ISAM
.author
Scott C Jacobs 
.version
1.01
.distribution
Shareware
.description
A Server/Library.  Even novice programmers can store/retrieve database
records.  Powerful, multi-"user", almost unlimited number/size of
records/files.  Different users may access same file, file/record locking
(exclusive/shared), multiple keys/ file.  Keys may: ascend/descend, overlap
each other, have unique/repeatable values, be up to 499 bytes.  Many record
retrieval methods.  Recover Index file if lost/corrupt.  Deleted record
space reclaimed.  Small: server < 49K; Resident Library < 8K.  AmigaDOS
V1.2 and up.  Contains examples w/source.  
